<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Frank O. Johnson was a Great Lakes working for the Morton Salt Company aboard the S.S. Covalt. He was from Ludington, Michigan.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The collection includes correspondence, reminiscences, and scrapbook of clippings largely concerning Great Lakes shipping, particularly Johnson's work for the Morton Salt Company. Logbooks, cashbook, and time and payroll books detail the operation of the Steamer Covalt. There are also a few photographs.</p>
</scopecontent>

